---
description: Angular templates — one line unless 5+ attributes
globs: frontend/**/*.{html,ts}
alwaysApply: false
---

# Angular template formatting

Keep an element on **one line** (opening tag + text + closing tag) when it has **≤ 4 attributes** and short content.

```html
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<a
  routerLink="/gallery"
  routerLinkActive="font-semibold"
  class="hover:underline"
>
  Gallery
</a>

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<a routerLink="/gallery" routerLinkActive="font-semibold" class="hover:underline">Gallery</a>
```

**Exception:** if an element has **more than 4 attributes**, put one attribute per line and indent the content.

```html
<!-- ✅ GOOD — 5 attributes -->
<button
  type="button"
  class="hover:text-neutral-900"
  [class.font-semibold]="locale() === 'uk'"
  [class.text-neutral-900]="locale() === 'uk'"
  (click)="setLocale( 'uk' )"
>
  UA
</button>
```

Container/layout elements with nested children stay multi-line for structure; the rule targets leaf / short-content elements, not flattening the whole tree.
